<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-993-458  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 993 458.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ESD: The Electronic System Design Magazine  Nov 1989 v19 n11p65(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multiprotocol processor marries 68000 and RISC. (Motorola'sMC68302 Integrated Multiprotocol Processor includesreduced-instruction-set computer controller)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, Arthur R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Motorola Corp's MC68302 Integrated Multiprotocol Processor (IMP)is a new member of the firm's MC683XX series of modular integratedmicrocontrollers.andP;  The MC68302 is based on Motorola's MC68000microprocessor combined with a reduced-instruction-set computer(RISC) controller.andP;  The new multiprotocol microcontroller isintended to facilitate multiprotocol communications support inIntegrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) terminal adapters.andP;  Thedevice includes serial channels with the capability of supportingHDLC, SDLC, bisynchronous, DDCMP and asynchronous communicationsprotocols; the RISC controller for managing buffer size; dual-portmemory; and DMA.andP;  The design and functioning of the MC68302, itsperipheral components and system glue devices are described.andO;Advantages of the design include the designer's ability to useavailable software development tools.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    MOTR.andO;Product:   Motorola 68302 (Microprocessor) (design and construction).andO;Topic:     Microprogrammed ControlMicroprocessorsReduced-Instruction-Set ComputersProcessor ArchitectureMultiprocessingControllers.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The 68302 Integrated Multiprotocol Processor. (chart)V.110 asynchronous-to-synchronous rate adaption. (chart)An ISDN voice-data terminal adapter 68302 IMP application. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>